task.summary: Added FlipCard as a children of DualCard, some cleanup
Removed the Clang-tidy recommended changes to defines, which broke the programme (LOWER_BOUND "6" -> LOWER_BOUND 6)
Added classes of Player and Deck. Restructured the project - adding a 'Source' folder for all the headers and cpp files.
Started working on Deck, created Hand that represents the cards playable by the player, drawn from the Deck card pool
Changed the vector in card play to a reference to a vector. Added playCard to the deck, which should call the play on the card and then move the card from the hand to the board.
Started work on the Card Loader utility, need to fix the parser.

WIP Turn. Need to figure out cards on board (history) whether it's going to be an array of cards or only their values. Having cards only would require to create new basic cards where effect is chosen and saving that into the array, values would be easily implemented. Probably the latter, as the cards themselves give no additional information and hence are redundant?
Considering changing Game::Player players[2] to a 2 element static array of pointers to players instead. Complete Game::round(), needs to be tested. Next up is Game::turn(). No documentation added.
Deck loading - directory's contents loaded, need to load individual files on the query.

Slight formatting adjustments. Moved all 'using namespace std' from header files to cpp files, adjusted header files with std:: prefix where necessary (most frequent were string, map, vector, ostream >> std:: string, map, vector, ostream)
Some namespace fixed. Parsing file for deck loading.
Decks are now loadable from files. Valid deck size check is needed at some point.
